# Faz 10: Performance Tuning

## Goal

Load test (`k6` @ 1000 concurrent) sonrası bottleneck'leri fix et. DB query optimization (index review, N+1 elimination). Redis caching strategy (expensive queries). Bundle size reduction. Lighthouse score improvement. Final SLO: P95 <500ms, error rate <0.1%, Lighthouse performance ≥80.

## Bu fazın çalışma modeli (iterasyonlar)

**Ölçmeden optimizasyon yok.** `@60-phase-10-performance` + **“Faz 10 — İterasyon N”**. Her chat’te en fazla **bir** ana bottleneck düzeltmesi + ölçüm tekrarı önerilir.

### İterasyon 1 — Baseline ölçüm

**Hedef:** k6 senaryosu + staging/prod-like ortamda baseline P95/error rate; Lighthouse ve bundle analyzer raporu **sadece okuma**; `docs/performance-tuning.md` içine “bulgular” bölümü aç.

**Bu iterasyonda yok:** Kod değişikliği (sadece gerekli enstrümantasyon — örn. slow query log açma — kabul).

**Stop:** [ ] Top 3 bottleneck listesi yazılı; [ ] önce/sonra metrik tablosu için şablon. PR/onay.

### İterasyon 2 — DB: index + N+1 + Prisma sorgu daraltma

**Hedef:** `pg_stat_statements` / slow log analizi; composite index; `select`/`include` revizyonu; DataLoader gerekliyse; integration’da query count assertion.

**Stop:** [ ] DB Done maddeleri (P95 <100ms hedefi doc ile); PR/onay.

### İterasyon 3 — Redis + API sıcak yollar + worker pool

**Hedef:** Master data + user lookup cache TTL; permission resolver hit rate doğrulama; response envelope/serialization ince ayar; BullMQ concurrency + pool tune.

**Stop:** [ ] Redis hit rate hedefleri; [ ] worker ayarları dokümante. PR/onay.

### İterasyon 4 — Frontend bundle + image/font + k6 final + dokümantasyon

**Hedef:** code split, tree-shake, `next/image`, `next/font`, memoization; final k6 1000 concurrent; regression perf testleri; `docs/performance-tuning.md` tamam.

**Stop:** Faz 10 Done Definition tamamı; roadmap işareti.

## Required Context

- `docs/08_TESTING_STRATEGY.md` Bölüm 8 (Load test + performance benchmarks)
- `docs/04_BACKEND_SPEC.md` — ilgili modüllerin query pattern'leri
- Auto-attached: 15-backend-database (query optimization patterns)

## Scope

### Backend optimizations

- DB index audit: slow query log analysis (pg_stat_statements)
- Composite index ekle (common filter + sort combinations)
- Prisma query analysis: `include` vs `select` review
- N+1 elimination: Prisma include + DataLoader pattern where applicable
- Redis caching: permission resolver (zaten var), master data (yeni — 10 dk TTL), user lookup (yeni — 2 dk)
- Response envelope optimization: omit undefined fields
- JSON serialization: precomputed for hot paths

### Frontend optimizations

- Bundle analysis: `@next/bundle-analyzer` report review
- Code split: route-level + feature-level chunks
- Tree-shaking: unused imports removal
- Image optimization: `next/image` everywhere (AVIF + responsive)
- Font optimization: `next/font` preload
- Prefetch strategy: link prefetch'i intentional yap
- React.memo + useMemo: expensive component re-renders analyze

### Worker optimizations

- BullMQ concurrency tune
- Email send batching (SES bulk API)
- DB connection pool tune per worker task

## Done Definition

- [ ] k6 load test: 1000 concurrent users, P95 <500ms, error <0.1%
- [ ] Lighthouse CI: critical 3 routes ≥80 performance, ≥90 a11y
- [ ] Bundle size: initial load ≤200 KB gzipped
- [ ] DB slow query log: all queries <100ms P95
- [ ] Redis hit rate: permission resolver >95%, master data >90%
- [ ] No N+1 detected in integration test DB query count
- [ ] Response time dashboard CloudWatch: P50 <200ms, P95 <500ms
- [ ] Error rate <0.1% (5xx, excluding client errors)
- [ ] Documented performance findings + fixes in `docs/performance-tuning.md`
- [ ] Regression test suite: performance tests for critical paths (P95 assertion)

## Explicit Don'ts

- Premature micro-optimization (measure first)
- Cache everything aggressively (staleness bug risk)
- Custom ORM / bypass Prisma for speed (maintainability cost)
- Read replicas MVP'de (Aurora writer yeter bu load'ta)
- CDN for API responses (cache-busting complex)
- Premature GraphQL migration (REST yeter)

## Related ADRs

- ADR-0030: Redis caching strategy (what to cache, TTL choices)
- ADR-0031: DB index policy (composite vs single-column)

